Filters:
    Filters are used to format the data accroding to application requirement.
    we have two types of filters.

        1. predefined filters
        2. custom filters

predefined filters:
    - the filters given by the framework called as predefined filters.

1. uppercase
    - this filter used to convert the lowercase characters to uppercase.

Ex.
    $scope.var_one="angularjs";
    {{var_one}} //angularjs
    {{var_one | uppercase}} //ANGULARJS



2. lowercase
    - this filter used to convert the uppercase characters to lowercase.
Ex.
    $scope.var_two = "NODEJS";

    {{var_two}} //NODEJS
    {{var_two | lowercase}}   //nodejs

3. currency
    - used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical values

Ex.
    $scope.var_three = 100;

    {{var_three}}  //100
    {{var_three | currency}}  //$100.00
    {{var_three | currency:"$":4}}   //$100.0000


4. orderBy
    - this filter used to arrange the data either assending or decending order.

5. limitTo
    - this filter used to display the required number of records from an array.

6. filter
    - this filter used to search the whole array based on user input.

Ex.
    $scope.var_four = [
                        {'id':1,'name':"Hello_1",'age':20},
                        {'id':5,'name':"Hello_5",'age':28},
                        {'id':2,'name':"Hello_2",'age':22},
                        {'id':4,'name':"Hello_4",'age':26},
                        {'id':3,'name':"Hello_3",'age':24}
    ];


    <input type="text" ng-model="search">
    <table border="1">
        <tr>
            <th>id</th>
            <th>name</th>
            <th>age</th>
        </tr>
        <tr ng-repeat="x in var_four | orderBy:'-id' | limitTo:3 | filter:search">
            <td>{{x.id}}</td>
            <td>{{x.name}}</td>
            <td>{{x.age}}</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

7.date
    - this filter used to format the date according to application requirement

Ex.
    $scope.var_five = new Date();

    {{var_five | date:'dd-MM-yy'}}
    {{var_five | date:'MM-dd-yy'}}
    {{var_five | date:'short'}}
    {{var_five | date:'medium'}}
    {{var_five | date:'fullDate'}}
    {{var_five | date:'shortTime'}}
        --
        --
        --


custom filters:
---------------
    - creatig our own filters based on application requirement called as custom filters.

Ex.
    {{"hello" | reverse}}

    app.filter("reverse",reverse);
    function reverse(){
        return function(arg1){
            var data = "";
            for(var i=0;i<arg1.length;i++){
                data = arg1[i]+data;
            }
            return data;
        }
    }

Ex.
    {{100 | my_currency:"â‚¹":true}}

    app.filter("my_currency",my_currency);
    function my_currency(){
        return function(amount,symbol,position){
            if(position){
                return symbol+" "+amount;
            }else{
                return amount+" "+symbol;
            }
        }
    }


























